image.altText: Anthony Albanese with Micaela Cronin.

props.synopsis: At a national cabinet meeting addressing the gendered violence crisis, the federal government commits more than $900 million for a program supporting women leaving violence, and a suite of online measures to combat online misogyny and young people viewing pornography.

title.children: The government has committed $1bn to combat the violence against women crisis. Here's what we know

image.altText: A woman holding a microphone speaks seriously.

props.synopsis: More than 200 Victorians at "serious risk" of family violence were sleeping in motels on Wednesday night, according to the head of a 24/7 family violence response centre.

title.children: Family violence advocates call for further action after $925m federal government pledge

image.altText: A man walks through journalists and cameras.

props.synopsis: Bruce Lehrmann has indicated he may appeal a Federal Court finding that on the balance of probabilities he raped Brittany Higgins.

title.children: Bruce Lehrmann set to appeal Federal Court defamation judgment

image.altText: Child works on a laptop computer

props.synopsis: The government is pursuing age verification for online porn. It's going to be complicated. Everyone agrees kids shouldn't be able to access porn online. Stopping them is much harder than you might think.

title.children: Three in four Australian children accessed porn before they turned 18. Here's how the government plans to tackle the problem

image.altText: Three large screens showa scene of a tree and paddock in the outback, within a black studio.

props.synopsis: What do Barbie, Dune, The Mandalorian and Melbourne's Victorian College of the Arts have in common? Using new cutting-edge technology to make films.

title.children: Technology used to film Barbie, Dune, The Mandalorian comes to Melbourne university

image.altText: A Qantas jumbo takes off

props.synopsis: Qantas resolves an issue with its app that allowed customers to view the details of other passengers, including names and upcoming flight plans.

title.children: Qantas apologises after app shows passengers' information to other travellers

image.altText: Peter Dutton speaks in a courtyard at Parliament House

props.synopsis: Peter Dutton says foreign interference poses a "significant threat" to Australia in the wake of revelations that Indian intelligence operatives were kicked out of the country in 2020.

title.children: Dutton says foreign interference poses 'significant threat' to Australia amid recent Indian spies revelations

image.altText: A long shot of an empty hotel corridor, with doors running along either side.

props.synopsis: Victoria's workplace safety watchdog says it is "deeply disappointed", after prosecutors dropped dozens of charges laid against the state government over its ill-fated COVID-19 hotel quarantine program.

title.children: Bid to prosecute Victorian government over COVID-19 hotel quarantine failures collapses in court

image.altText: An urgent care centre

props.synopsis: Staff at Colac Area Health posed as patients to make its urgent care ward look busy during a visit from the health minister. At least one ambulance was also arranged to arrive during the visit.

title.children: Regional Victorian hospital staff used ambulance and posed as patients in elaborate ruse during minister's visit

image.altText: Two formally-dressed women walk next to each other with a man walking near them.

props.synopsis: Pauline Hanson's legal team tenders a video of her telling Derryn Hinch to leave Australia in her defence against allegations of racial discrimination against senator Mehreen Faruqi.

title.children: Video of Pauline Hanson telling white former senator to 'go back to New Zealand' used in racial discrimination defence

image.altText: Demonstrators clash at UCLA.

props.synopsis: Student protests over the Israel-Gaza war expand to an increasing number of college campuses in the United States, with Australian students joining the camp-outs demanding that their educational institutions cut ties with Israel.

title.children: Riot police enter Columbia University to end pro-Palestinian encampment as movement takes hold in Australia

image.altText: a woman in a hospital bed taking a selfie

props.synopsis: Medical bills examined by experts reveals how Australian chronic pain sufferers are being apparently billed for fictitious services, inflated costs, and treatments for conditions they don't have.

title.children: 'I feel violated, I trusted them': Patients appalled after being shown the true nature of their medical bills

image.altText: Canberra gendered violence rally

props.synopsis: The footage of Anthony Albanese at a gendered violence rally outside Parliament House is nearly unwatchable. How can a political leader — whose entire skill set is supposed to be about competent judgement under fire — get it so horribly wrong?

title.children: 'I am the prime minister' should never be uttered by anyone. Albanese chose the worst possible moment

image.altText: Don Pyke speaks to the media in 2019.

props.synopsis: Essendon and Collingwood back the lead of Don Pyke in condemning violence against women, as the AFL confirms the code will make a statement on the issue at matches this weekend.

title.children: AFL clubs support stance on gendered violence as Eagles boss Pyke highlights 'horrendous' numbers

image.altText: A man stands during this year's Anzac Day service in Albany. He's wearing a suit.

props.synopsis: The Liberal Party's Albany branch has endorsed Dr Thomas Brough as its candidate for next year's state election, despite a recent history of controversial public commentary.

title.children: Liberal Party preselects WA councillor who linked queer community to paedophiles

image.altText: Two men sit talking

props.synopsis: Chris Minns pays tribute to his father, the man he has previously said introduced him to the "Labor tribe", following confirmation of his death.

title.children: NSW premier's father dies days after suffering heart attack

image.altText: A composite image of four fair-skinned men, three of whom are in military uniform.

props.synopsis: Captain Danniel Lyon's wife tells an inquiry into last year's fatal Taipan crash she believes it was cruel to give families hope amid the search effort.

title.children: 'Someone is going to die': Widow tells inquiry airman raised safety concerns before fatal Taipan chopper crash

image.altText: A colourful graphic featuring a TV icon, a teen girl, a remote, and ABC, SBS, Nine, Seven, Netflix, Disney+ and other logos.

props.synopsis: Ratings data shows young people are turning away from traditional TV in droves in favour of streaming platforms and social media. But an expert says free-to-air television still has a role, and Australia does have a choice about its media future.

title.children: In the age of streaming and social media, do we still need free-to-air TV?

image.altText: A large fish washed up on a South Australian beach.

props.synopsis: A huge creature of the deep estimated to be more than two metres long that washed up on a South Australian beach is "almost certainly" a bump-head sunfish, the state's museum says.

title.children: Huge fish believed to be giant sunfish washes up on SA beach

image.altText: drone shot of large collection of caravans gathered around a stage on a big patch of land

props.synopsis: With pop-focused music festivals like Splendour in the Grass and Groove in the Moo calling it quits, family-friendly, smaller festivals in unique locations are thriving.

title.children: What can the Mundi Mundi Bash tell us about the future of music festivals in modern Australia?

image.altText: A close up shot of a sold sign outside of a property in the Albany Suburb of Mira mar

props.synopsis: Surprisingly strong inflation, but exceptionally weak retail spending, has major bank economists predicting the Reserve Bank won't cut interest rates until November.

title.children: Big four banks warn first rate cut won't come until November, as 'incredibly strong' migration makes the RBA's task 'more difficult'

image.altText: Matthew Farrell smiles looking at the camera while sitting in the cockpit of a small aeroplane.

props.synopsis: A Victorian coroner has criticised a peak aviation body after new evidence appeared to show it had withheld documents outlining concerns around licensing a pilot who fatally crashed his plane.

title.children: Inquest into pilot's death hears accusations of 'cover-up' as documents allegedly withheld

image.altText: An aerial view of suburban Adelaide.

props.synopsis: Data from CoreLogic shows house prices rising for the 15th straight month in April. Here's what property prices look like across the country.

title.children: House prices have risen for the 15th month in a row. Here's what property values look like across the country

image.altText: an outside view of a row of houses

props.synopsis: Property prices surged once again in April due the ongoing shortage of housing and rising demand. Could the rise of the YIMBY — or the "yes in my back yard" — movement be the solution to boosting the supply of affordable housing?

title.children: 'I want the best in my backyard': Why generations don't see eye to eye on boosting housing supply

image.altText: A calico cat standing up with its tail raised.

props.synopsis: Galena found herself at the centre of a stressful trip in an Amazon package, a feverish search, a California rescue and a tearful reunion.

title.children: Housecat who enjoys exploring cardboard boxes accidentally posted 860km in Amazon order return

image.altText: Peter Foott in the drivers seat of the truck

props.synopsis: With the take-up of electric vehicles across Australia commercial market considered "pretty modest" so far, those supporting an EV garbage truck trial in Shepparton believe its important to start chipping away towards a transition.

title.children: Electric garbage truck trialled in regional Australia drives 'like a limousine'

image.altText: Jo Harten holds a netball in both hands

props.synopsis: Netball Australia is already embracing changes to their traditional playing dress, but the Super Netball clubs are yet to take up the offer. Giants co-captain Jo Harten says she is pushing hard to make it happen.

title.children: 'I'd be brave enough to change': Super Netball captain hoping to ditch the dress

image.altText: Cash being handed away by an elderly person

props.synopsis: What if the government was doing everything it could to stop thieves making off with our money, except the one thing that could really work?

title.children: Could new rules in the UK help solve Australia's scam crisis?

image.altText: Steve Smith in Australia's ODI kit

props.synopsis: Steve Smith is left out of an Australian World Cup squad for the first time since 2012 as Australia's 15-man provisional squad is named.

title.children: 'Tailored approach': Smith axed as Australia unveils T20 World Cup squad

image.altText: A women's soccer team wearing green uniforms walks out under a red banner gesturing to their heads

props.synopsis: FIFA threatens the country with suspension amid accusations of money laundering and "undue influence by third parties" within its federation.

title.children: Matildas' Olympic opponents Zambia could be disqualified from Games

image.altText: Rubbish is strewn across the grass

props.synopsis: A pool lined with green sludge, rotting roofs and termite infested buildings – this derelict island resort has become a sad tourist attraction for all the wrong reasons, and it's not an isolated case.

title.children: Once a mecca for the rich and famous, these island resorts now lie in ruins

image.altText: A bishop is speaking into a mic as a woman behind him holds a phone and interrupts him

props.synopsis: A protester interrupts the Archbishop of Sydney less than a minute after he had begun comments over his concerns over legislation designed to provide greater protections to transgender people in New South Wales.

title.children: Bill to allow trans people to change gender on driving licence escalates after Archbishop raises concerns about 'anti-religious undercurrent'

image.altText: Aliir Aliir is slung to the ground in a tackle by Jack Higgins

props.synopsis: St Kilda forward Jack Higgins will miss the next three weeks after failing to either overturn or reduce his suspension for a dangerous sling tackle.

title.children: Jack Higgins fails to overturn three-match ban for dangerous tackle on Aliir Aliir

image.altText: Toyah Cordingley sits with her dogs.

props.synopsis: During a pre-trial hearing for murder accused Rajwinder Singh, the Supreme Court hears that 24-year-old Toyah Cordingley had started a secret relationship with her podiatrist in the weeks before her death and believed her partner knew "something was off".

title.children: Cairns woman Toyah Cordingley in secret relationship before her alleged murder, court hears

image.altText: An impression of large white wind turbines in the ocean

props.synopsis: Federal Minister for Climate Change and Energy Chris Bowen officially unveils the first proponents to receive offshore wind farm feasibility licences.

title.children: Australia one step closer to generating electricity from offshore wind farms as projects receive feasibility licences
